[SN]TITLE[SN]
First responder saves newborn baby in Loughborough

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A Loughborough student who had recently completed his training as a community responder has saved the life of a day-old baby.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
27 January 2015 Last updated at 10:56 GMT
Mike Hardy was called to a home of Joaquim and Patricia Rodrigues where their new-born daughter had stopped breathing and was choking.
Jo Healey reports.
